During the course students read and discuss different texts on early childhood education as well as other educational issues and get to know the related vocabulary. The topics include: early years teachers and their work, pre-school curriculum and related topics, children's development, play and toys, special educational needs and inclusive education, studying at university and good learning practice, etc. Students read speciality-related (scientific) texts and make a literature review (autumn term) and an oral presentation (spring term).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To enlarge students` vocabulary and develop their language skills on B2 language levels in order to prepare students for independent work with literature in the field of pre-school and general education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student: - knows essential vocabulary in the field of education and comprehends speciality-related texts; - discusses educational issues within the range of the vocabulary acquired; - summarises and paraphrases educational texts; - compiles and makes an oral presentation on speciality-related literature; - analyses and gives feedback on peers' presentations.
